        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-08-24T21:54:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To match what we do everywhere else I think this should be const ref and then make a copy of it (for reasons described in the comment below) to call validate_backend_texture with. Even though this essentially does a copy, eventually when the gpu backend gets cleaned up to where we don\u0027t need the copy, then we will want this to be a const ref, so we should have that be the API from the start. Plus we\u0027re doing extra copies passing this through from SkImage calls to the SkImage_Gpu calls",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 456,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 456,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "983f89e792232fc919e38e6520e7d6acc9ee8754",
